President Obama announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key Administration posts. Thelma Duggin, President of the AnBryce Foundation, will be appointed as a Member of the Board of Trustees of the Woodrow Wilson International Center for Scholars. Marcia Cruz-Correa, an Associate Professor of Medicine and Biochemistry at the University of Puerto Rico, will be appointed as a Member of the National Cancer Advisory Board. Kevin J. Cullen, currently the Director of the Marlene and Stewart Greenebaum Cancer Center at the University of Maryland, will also be appointed as a Member of the National Cancer Advisory Board. Olufunmilayo Falusi Olopade, the Walter L. Palmer Distinguished Service Professor of Medicine & Human Genetics at the University of Chicago, will be appointed as a Member of the National Cancer Advisory Board. Lastly, Jonathan M. Samet, Professor and Flora L. Thornton Chair of the Department of Preventive Medicine at the University of Southern California, and Bill Sellers, Vice President and Global Head of Oncology for the Novartis Institutes of BioMedical Research, will both be appointed as Members of the National Cancer Advisory Board. President Obama expressed his confidence in their abilities and looks forward to working with them in the future.